The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Midnapore, Jan. 1: A CPM leader was killed by suspected Maoists in a West Midnapore village about 15km from the Orissa border.    
	Police said Bhagbat Singh, 52, was having his dinner tonight when a gang stormed into his house and shot him point blank. Singh was the secretary of the partys Kamalapukuria local committee.     
	The is the first time a possible Maoist strike has taken place in the Nayagram area, about 130km from Lalgarh.        
	Bolpur: Union finance minister Pranab Mukherjee has ended the CPMs 32-year run in the governing body of a college in his home district, Birbhum. He was elected its president yesterday. Seven of the 11 members of the body voted for Mukherjee. The Left-backed nominee, Maya Sadhu, got only four votes. Biman Chowdhury, the principal of Abhedananda Mahavidyalaya in Sainthia, 250 km from Calcutta, said Mukherjee had agreed to enter the fray because of a request from former Birbhum district Congress chief Nihar Dutta.        
	Calcutta: Four Left parties have written to Prime Minister Manmohan Singh requesting him to declare January 23 as Desh Prem Diwas on the occasion of the 112th birth anniversary of Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose. Forward Bloc state secretary Asok Ghosh said the party had been requesting the Centre to declare January 23, Netajis birthday, as Desh Prem Diwas since 1996. This time, the general secretaries of the CPM, CPI, and the RSP have also written to the Prime Minister in this regard.                                                                                                                                                      
